The couple claims a gang of five men robbed them, while Ster-Kinekor says in a statement that its investigations have found that one criminal is responsible. JOHANNESBURG - Police are investigating a case of robbery after a couple was robbed inside a Ster-Kinekor cinema in Rosebank. It’s understood the crime happened over the weekend at The Zone Shopping Mall. The couple claims a gang of five men robbed them, while Ster-Kinekor says in a statement that its investigations have found that one criminal is responsible. The police’s Bongi Mdletshe said: “We’re currently investigating the matter in terms of what transpired during the robbery. The suspects are still at large. Two cellphones were taken during the robbery. Anyone who has information regarding this matter is requested to contact Rosebank SA Police Service.”